sql: SELECT MIN(an.name) AS alternative_name, MIN(chn.name) AS voiced_character_name, MIN(n.name) AS voicing_actress, MIN(t.title) AS american_movie FROM aka_name AS an, char_name AS chn, cast_info AS ci, company_name AS cn, movie_companies AS mc, name AS n, role_type AS rt, title AS t WHERE ci.note  in ('(voice)', '(voice: Japanese version)', '(voice) (uncredited)', '(voice: English version)') AND cn.country_code ='[us]' AND n.gender ='f' and n.name like '%An%' AND rt.role ='actress' AND ci.movie_id = t.id AND t.id = mc.movie_id AND ci.movie_id = mc.movie_id AND mc.company_id = cn.id AND ci.role_id = rt.id AND n.id = ci.person_id AND chn.id = ci.person_role_id AND an.person_id = n.id AND an.person_id = ci.person_id;
